    <description>&amp;quot;Storm over Hengyang 1944 (&amp;#232;&amp;#161;&amp;#161;&amp;#233;&amp;#153;&amp;#189;&amp;#233;&amp;#162;&amp;#168;&amp;#230;&amp;#154;&amp;#180;1944)&amp;quot; is a two-player board wargame that simulates the defense of Hengyang in late stage of Ichigo Operation, June 24 to August 8, 1944.&amp;#10;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defense_of_Hengyang&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn represents 1 week and each area is about 1 km across. One player commands the Imperial Japanese Army&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#136;&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#167;&amp;#230;&amp;#151;&amp;#165;&amp;#230;&amp;#156;&amp;#172;&amp;#229;&amp;#184;&amp;#157;&amp;#229;&amp;#156;&amp;#139;&amp;#233;&amp;#153;&amp;#184;&amp;#232;&amp;#187;&amp;#141;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#137;and the other player commands the National Revolutionary Army&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#136;&amp;#229;&amp;#156;&amp;#139;&amp;#230;&amp;#176;&amp;#145;&amp;#233;&amp;#157;&amp;#169;&amp;#229;&amp;#145;&amp;#189;&amp;#232;&amp;#187;&amp;#141;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#137;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In SoH, each player uses leader points to activate units in each area for moving or firing. In each turn, each player draws tactic markers respectively and roll for initiative. The units includes infantry, artillery, mortar, and engineer. The NRA side needs to hold two areas in the Hengyang City for 7 turns to win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The components includes one 22*34 inches map and 180 5/8 inch die-cut counters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
